rComments: A bad finance professor. Lessons are super boring; I had to speed up the lecture recordings to 2x to listen to them. I feel like the DGD assistants were only reading the answers already provided in the book, they seemed to know little about the material. This professor demands more than he teaches.

don't...just don't. this guy cannot teach for his life, left me and pretty much the whole class confused and probably even less educated on finance than beforehand. Jumps into concepts way too fast with zero emphasis on the basics and foundation of finance. Have fun failing and getting dumber and more stressed with this Akyol kid.

If you have enrolled in his class for whatever semester, then my suggestion is that you either live with the low grade or wait until another prof teaches this class. His teaching is confusing and irrelevant to any of the quizzes or exams. He seldom provides help to students who don't understand the concepts and simply wants to end the class ASAP.

rComments: One of the worst profs. The way he explains practice problems make no sense and doesn’t outline how to get other variables needed to solve the problem. Midterm exam is rough and real time crunch (nothing like dgd or quiz). First quiz was easy but midterm and final tg are worth 75% of your grade.

This prof neither increases your knowledge on Finance nor helps improve your GPA. The quality of learning is 0 with him since he will disappear like a ghost after first few weeks. He makes the class unnecessarily hard despite teaching so little. Telfer really needs some quality control of profs now. Did this prof get his PhD at Walmart or amazon?

rComments: If this is a mandatory class for you and there is no other prof teaching it for the sem, WAIT IT OUT. Took his class online, saw the guy the first week, and after that AWOL. He posts pre-recorded lectures of him just reading the slides, replies to most of our emails with a "thx but no thx" attitude, and gives the toughest quizzes out there.

This prof should go back to university and take a course about how to be a teacher. 99% of his explanation on the course concepts is vague and useless, leading to your destined failure in assignments and exams. The fact that Telfer cannot find better profs to teach this mandatory class makes me chunder. U better hire a tutor or study 10x harder.

The first rating of 5/5 is misleading and I was misled to pick this course. To future students taking this, make sure you have strong understanding on the basics of finance such as CAPM, etc. If not, you are going to struggle in this class.
